article.headline: Coastal Carolina 64, Winthrop 50
article.story: CONWAY, S.C. (AP) -- Pele Paelay had 19 points and seven rebounds as Coastal Carolina swept the season series from Winthrop with a 64-50 win Saturday. The Chanticleers (11-9, 5-4 Big South Conference) have won three of their last five against the Eagles. During that time, no other Big South team has been able to beat Winthrop (14-6, 8-2). The Eagles hit the first bucket of the game, then led just once more the Chanticleers held Winthrop to its lowest point total of the season. Coastal Carolina was up 11 at half, but the Eagles took a 43-41 lead with 11 minutes to go. The Chanticleers then went on a 12-2 run to take a 53-45 lead with 7:34 to go. A 3-pointer by Winthrop's Torrell Martin cut the deficit to 53-50 with 6:30 to go, but the Eagles would not score again. The Chanticleers made 10 of their 23 3-pointers, while Winthrop shot 4-of-19 behind the arc. The loss put the Eagles a game behind first place Birmingham-Southern in the Big South. The higher seeded team hosts the title game in the Big South tournament. Moses Sonko and Jack Leasure each added 14 points and Colin Stevens had 10 assists for Coastal Carolina. Martin led Winthrop with 13 points, while Bradshaw and James Shuler each added 10.
